cui_name: Stage IV Breast Cancer AJCC v6 and v7
reasoning: Stage IV breast cancer (metastatic disease) using AJCC v6/v7 staging criteria. Stage IV definition remains consistent across AJCC versions as metastatic disease. Incidence ~5.1 per 100k based on proportion of stage IV cases at diagnosis.
source: Edge SB et al. (2010). AJCC Cancer Staging Manual (7th ed.). Springer-Verlag
